This has become my go-to stir fry sauce template. I don't have the dried mushrooms on hand so I use chicken stock instead, and use various vegetables in the stir fry (tonight it was onion, carrot, celery, red pepper, snow peas,bok choy, asparagus. Can use beef or chicken instead of shrimp. Very tasty.

Rating: 4
This was my first recipe using fermented black beans - I got my first packet this week. I didn't have shrimp, so I made this with chicken, used mirin instead of sherry, and at the end, added some szechuan peppercorns. It was outstanding. I'm going to try this with pork next, but lobster is also a great idea.

