Rating: 4
I am quite surprised at the reviews that said this was bland. I used dry salted black beans as recipe called for not black bean sauce and it was delicious. The only thing I am going to try next time is to add an additional tablespoon of the black beans and less ginger and garlic as I prefer the taste of the black beans and oyster sauce over that of the ginger and garlic.

Rating: 4
I didn't have white wine so I used sake instead and I added carrots and peas for flavor. I put it all over soba noodles for a healthy option. One word: delicious. My husband and children loved it.

Rating: 4
At last I've found an authentic black bean sauce. I can't stop making it! It's great over clams, as well. Steam the clams open first, set aside, and substitute the clam juice for the mushroom water. Also, in a stir fry with chinese pea pods, tofu, and black mushrooms. Be careful not to add too much sherry. It alters the taste dramatically with even slight overusage. This one is the real deal.

Rating: 4
This is my new favorite recipe. Tried it the first time with prepared black bean sauce and found it overly salty and metallic. Gave it another try with the called-for fermented black beans and it was just terrific. I simply don't understand those who said it was bland and tasteless. I find myself craving this and have been making it exactly as written, except for more heat, about twice a month for the past three months. Simple to prepare (but a lot of bowls to wash) and very, very tasty.

